hopobject.body: A law firm haladrugstore.com The feud between Quinn, House Speaker Michael Madigan, and Senate President John Cullerton has overshadowed negotiations on the pension issue. The battle is complicated by the upcoming 2014 gubernatorial election in which Quinn faces a primary challenge from President Barack Obama's former chief of staff William Daley, the son and brother of Chicago mayors. Several Republicans have also announced they are running for governor.
